			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I submitted this to the Dev team, I am sure it will be used as toliet paper or to paper the cage of Ralph the wonder chinchilla office pal at SoE.
<br />

<br />
------------------------------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />

<br />
This is a long post and it deals with a few issues concerning the magician class.
<br />

<br />
I have spent a considerable amount of time in BoT after the recent patch with my level 65 magician.  Currently I am around 2 experience blues down from the numerous deaths me and my friends have experienced trying to kill tower named mobs.  These MOBs did not require a medium raid force before since level 65 Enchanter and Magician charms were used to charm mobs for added damage.
<br />

<br />
What is clear to us is that 2 or 3 groups of players that are not in the very best gear and are all level 65 will simply not be able to raid the tower now that high level charm is useless.
<br />

<br />
The changes to the high level charms now make it impossible to use them in any beneficial way.  If charm breaks during a fight the charm caster is dead.
<br />

<br />
My suggestion is that the development team work on replacement spells to replace the level 65 charm spells.  There is no need to take them out of the game since I believe they are completely worthless.  I moved mine to the back of my spell book.  While I cannot speak for other classes I know that I would love to see one or a combination of the following done for the Magician class to compensate for the fact the level 65 elemental charm is now a complete waste of space:
<br />

<br />
1.  A snare spell for mages (will help us solo since that is evidently what you want us to be doing since no one is grouping us in PoP now without Charm being even remotely useful).
<br />
2.  Fix the level 63 fire pet so that it actually casts a Varity of nice spells and is worthy of being a level 63rd pet.  Maybe letting it cast damage spells of magic, ice, and fire base as well as the root it does now?
<br />
3.  Increase the power (damage output and mitigation) of all level 61+ mage pets so that they are indeed useful in PoP encounters.
<br />
4.  Upgrade the magician epic pet so that it is also level 60  (the pet is not exactly free since the mage epic is the hardest).
<br />

<br />
These upgrades may seem to be overpowering but I think that the Magician class has had enough problems finding exp groups and in general exp when groups could not be found.  Mages are the most undesired class in the game when it comes to PoP exp groups and this is a serious problem since we are also unable to solo very well at all.
<br />

<br />
You have taken away the 1 spell/ability that has been giving level 65 mages exp group invites for months now.  I have seen first hand how useless this spell has become in one patch.  Enchanters, Necromancers, and Druids are not nearly as badly affected because they have other skills to help them group or solo many times better then the magician.
<br />

<br />
Even with charm working as it did before I died daily at least a few times when I was grouped.  It came with great risk and now its simply broken.
<br />

<br />
What frustrates me the most is that throughout pop exp zones the "perfect core group" is strongly encouraged.  This leaves out several classes to fend for themselves in regards to experience and 1 of those classes just does not have the skills to solo.  While that class does decent damage and summons half decent items they are thought of as a benefit to raids more then anything else since group spots are at a premium and are needed for the slowers, healers, tanks, and efficient damage dealers (rogues, rangers, monks).
<br />

<br />
This leaves that 1 class that cannot offer any one benefit to a perspective group that another class can do better but cannot solo without tremendous risk out in the cold with LFG on for hours.  This class is the magician.  A guild mate of mine compared the class jokingly to a used car which the owner had dumped too much money into for repairs.  While the owner was unhappy with the cars performance he did not have the resources to get a new car.
<br />

<br />
If I knew this would be the end of the magician class after around 3 years of play I would never have selected it and spent the sweat, tears, and effort to build him up to level 65.  I always had some hope that it would change for the better.  With PoP I saw some of my hopes realized but now I see more of the same.
<br />

<br />
Please do something to balance mages against their group desirability level.  If you make it so we can solo for exp again many would be happy enough to receive some decent AA progression in between raids and simply let the "core" classes have their groups.
<br />

<br />
If nothing is done you can only loose more customers to the incoming new MMOGs, while the magician class community is hardly the size of the Druid or Enchanter it still represents a community of decent players that have decided to make the magician their main character.  With the exception of the diehard few the class is on the verge of extinction.<br />_________________<br />Sage Rthen Majere
<br />
Arch Covoker
<br />
Master of the Orb</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
