			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have no clue what is up with other mages having trouble LFG.  The ONLY reason I can see is maybe levels... Almost daily I log on to EQ and get offers for groups within 5-10 minutes of getting online.  I spend a majority of my time unanon and non-roleplay, so it's obvious that someone was doing a "/who mag 65" or something of that nature.  
<br />

<br />
If I put /lfg on and let it sit as such while I'm goofing off with tradeskills or attempting to solo in Storms, I'll get several offers for groups in Valor and such.  The "charm group" tells don't come very often, though I still occasionally get requests for me to come and be a pet wrangler for BoT groups (I'm guessing the xp loss from the nerf doesn't outway the rate of xp with the pet there).  A few of those are people that have grouped with me in the past and might just like my nature, but they admittingly take me over wizards, monks, and rogues as a DD for their experience group.  When I leave these groups, they almost ALWAYS try and seek out another mage to take my place over any other class.  
<br />

<br />
On balancing the class...  
<br />

<br />
I will agree that the 63 fire pet needs some work, and maybe the 65 earth could be looked at (though not much they could do short of adjusting his damage mitigation would help).  The earth pet has NEVER been able to mitigate or dodge damage very well in his lower levels, so there is no reason they should change it for the level 65 version.  I know we'll never get a snare, seeing how only two classes in the game get that spell (druids and wizards, of which only one has become a "utility" spell).  Slow we'll never get because it wouldn't really "fit" into our spell list very well.  If we got either of the last two at all they would have to be indirect effects added to another type of summoned weapon (or added as a component of the current selection).  The only way they could really give us a way to resort to pet soloing non-caster mobs would be to upgrade our armor summoning line or tweak the heck out of pet mitigation (they already are powerful beasts as it is).  
<br />

<br />
The only "problem" we're talking about is that we can't solo very well in PoP zones.  Well, it all depends on HOW you're trying to solo for one.  I can solo tier 2 just fine, though I have to restrict myself to caster mobs.  I can solo in ANY tier 1 zone, just not every mob in those zones.  But that issue as been discussed.  Don't look at the pet as flawed because he can't tank 300-ish melee hits unless the mob is slowed--no class currently CAN tank those hits unslowed very well, and even when they can not very well unless they have other classes there to heal them.  Asking for our pets to be given this ability would be a slap in the face to the pure PC melee classes.  Our pets are amazing tools as they are.  They outdmg or come very close to equal compared to the "average" reprsentation of most of the melee classes.  Of course given proper equipment monks and rogues will outdmg our pets, but that has to be expected.  If you compare them with everyone else they do what they're supposed to quite well.  Directly increasing their potency would overpower us by quite a bit and probably wouldn't fix the problems we're whining about.
<br />

<br />
At this time here are *my* current issues with our class.  I'm not saying we're a flawed class, but just giving my idea of what I think our problems are:
<br />

<br />
*  63 fire pet really needs some work.  No one I know who has this pet can think of a real use to bring him out aside from impressing lower levels and in duels for fun.  Get rid of his root and give him at least equal or better nukes than his 52 and 58 counterparts (as it is he randomly casts a 75 dmg stun which is worse than the 61 air's stun).  
<br />

<br />
*  Upgrade the potency of some of our heal spells (to just under what Beastlords get) OR decrease/remove the reuse time on them.  ATM the only way that I can conceivably hold my pet up against a mob is memming 52 and 64 pet heals and chaining them like mad.  If I EVER see the level 60 heal I'm sure it would replace the 52 quite well but it would be nice to either see the heals upgraded to meet the Beastlord versions or even have the casting delay removed altogether.  It would merely give us another way of using our mana when we solo (for those that love to play healer for the pet).  
<br />

<br />
*  If we're goign to get snare or slow it should be in the form of another procing weapon or added as a component of the current weapons.  Perhaps the Blade of Walnan could have a 15% snare component and Blade of the Kedge could have a 15% slow component.  I'm not saying we necessarily need slow or snare, but I don't think we should get either as an extra spell in the book UNLESS they added one or the other to our 44 and 55 DoTs.  
<br />

<br />
*  This was suggested some other place, but give us a higher level upgrade to our "summon phantom" armor line.  The armor could be pet only (like muzzles, weapons, and belt) and have added hp's and stats (possibly different values based on the actual piece of armor) along with equal AC to the lower level phantom armor line.  The total HP bonus for ALL the pieces could add up to around at most 500 hp's or so, which would give our pet a little more buffer before he dies by wearing a girdle, 2 weapons, and a full suit of the phantom armor.  I would only suggest one type of armor (it could be "Summon Phantom Ethreal Armor" or something), but different types could have different properties (i.e. different bonuses to resists for each type, etc.).  
<br />

<br />
*  If possible remove pets and other npcs from being able to exist on a rampage list.  It is almost guaranteed that they die against mobs that have high melee and rampage frequently, so this would help immensely against those types of mobs.  
<br />

<br />
*  Possibly add AA's to ALL classes as a "bonus" to the game, just like they add new zones for free once in a blue moon.  Warriors could get the added aggro/taunt AA's they never got--other classes just some little enhancements.  For the mages, we would get 4 different types of pet "focus" AA's (one for each type of pet and 3 ranks of power) along with maybe a timer decrease for Frenzied Burnout and Host of the Elements.  The main idea of this would be the focus AA's for the pets, which would maybe add something like 2/4/7% to that pet's total hp's, a certain amount of damage mitigation, resists (maybe), and some form of increasing the pet's damage (Earth = melee damage increase, Fire = nuke damage increase, Water = backstab damage increase, Air = erm... haven't a clue yet).  
<br />

<br />
Again, I honestly think we're doing alright as far as a class IN RELATION TO OTHER CLASSES.  In the grand scheme of things we are capable of performing our intended job--to deal out damage.  Whether we do this via the pet, DD's, DS's, summoned focuses for ourselves as well as other casters, or by handing out mana rods, we are doing quite well.  If they did anything to increase our pet's power, or anything at all, they would have to rebalance the classes as a whole unless they tweaked us indirectly like the suggestions above.  I'm not saying this from the point of view of the "uber" crowd, because I am very far from being there.  I'm speaking from the POV of a casual experience group homebody mage (which I humbly admit to being).<br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062" taret=_blank>Sage Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a>
<br />
Arch Convoker of Solusek Ro
<br />
<a href="http://www.furiouspantaloons.org"><i>Furious Pantaloons</i></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
