				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I honestly do not care if someone puts a label on my statements such as "class envy" (after all, as a woman I am supposed to have penis envy, don't feel it a bit). Comparing our class to BL does not have to have anything to do with class envy, just a straightforward comparison of one class to another. Their pet is almost as powerful if not better than ours, they have slow, they have better heal, to me it makes no sense why we should not get as good a pet heal to compensate for lack of slow. Period, take it or leave it.
<br />

<br />
As Razmatazz said, its pretty clear that 50% slow means doubling the power of heal. If you don't get me, try understanding other people.
<br />

<br />
And you may have had BL slow from level 22, but slow does not truly shine in its full power till you get to mobs that hit 300+. Mage pets do not stand up well to that kind of beating, well at least not solo. Which makes us  resort to cahining pets, which makes our efficiency go down the drain, as we can't use pet buffs or gear (as pets will die most of the time faster than one can buff them). In tier one that still does not get that bad, but in tier two it is bad. So being able to use pet buffs and pet weapons requires that we have some means of keeping pet alive during fight, i.e. better pet heal.
<br />

<br />
Classes that adopted succesfully to tier two have one thing in common: they avoid getting hit for that insane amount of damage, either by reducing it with slow, or keeping mobs away by snare kiting. If you have not had experinece in tier two, that may not make that much sense, but thats just the way most people experienced it. Take it or leave it, or level us and try, whatever.
<br />

<br />
Taking apart my straightforward comparison of classes by using some psychological instead of game reasons makes me want to just end this conversation right here, so if you want to discuss something please refrain from labeling and/or outdated Freudian analysis and use the facts from EQ.
<br />

<br />
Edit:
<br />

<br />
