<br />

<br />
That line is fundamental to the mage class.
<br />

<br />
The loss of tankable pets supported only by its master may be critical.  I am still mulling over how best to present the problem and a spectrum of solutions.
<br />

<br />
Slow is clearly one of the most powerful direct abilities in the game.  It multiplies the group's hitpoints as well as the value of all heals.  It is so powerful, that before <span style="font-style: italic">Planes of Power</span>, many clerics despaired because slow was so much better than cleric heals allone, that if one could only have one priest in the group, the shaman appeared the obvious choice.  Or put another way, with a shaman, there was very little need for a cleric.
<br />

<br />
Slow is an obvious solution to tankability.  I am not saying it is the right solution, but anyone who does not expect some mages to suggest it is fooling themselves.  Slow is exactly what allows beastlords to solo through pet-tanking, while archmages only barely can.
<br />

