			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I can't say I really understand the original poster's complaint. It sounds ... over the top, sorry.
<br />

<br />
I am not in anybody's book 'uber equipped'. I am in a very tiny guild (only two active players these days). Yes, I am level 65 now, but I don't have many of my spectrals, and I have none of my rune spells (well, I didn't have until yesterday when I finally won one and got CotAM). And yes, I spend long periods, sometimes a few hours, LFG. I am in Europe, on a server which is predominently US populated, so low population makes grouping for damage dealing classes harder. The main problem is finding a *&%$ slower sometimes, 'slow' is so important in PoP, perhaps overly so.
<br />

<br />
And yet, I cannot share the doom-and-gloom of the original poster here. The magician class is VERY POWERFUL. I find, when a group in BoT or PoV or similar is looking for a damage dealer, if there are people who have grouped with me before, I get snapped up. Magi can get a reputation as excellent damage dealers, and I know a significant number of players who will take a mage over a second rogue or ranger or monk any day, and I get the feedback from strangers I group with, that when they have seen the damage a mage can put out, they are happy to take them in future groups. I'm not talking about pet groups here, hell, I have no interest in those (if they even exist, I never see them); I am talking about your average standard balanced groups, in which the magician class can easily be placed.
<br />

<br />
Yes, I agree totally its sad we cannot solo anymore for at least a little XP in competitive zones. Yes, I would like it if we had that ability restored to us, even in some minor way (eg pet-equipped slow-effect DS item).
<br />

<br />
But we are very far from weak or undesired.
<br />

<br />
I had a real drive for XP this last long weekend. I had one BoT group after another, all day Friday, Sunday and Monday, and made a total of just over 9 AAXP points (and bought QS2 and QS3 from this).
<br />

<br />
Really, I don't think we are any worse off than most other classes regarding group desirability. OK, 'slow'-casters, especially enchanters, get groups in minutes, but the 'getting-groups' issue is not easier for most other classes than it is for ours.
<br />

<br />
Suzanna.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
